commit.message:
syscall-linux.c: don't include <sys/io.h>

Seems the <sys/io.h> header isn't used for anything, but it breaks build
on platforms, where it is not available.
pci.c: unmagick arg{1,2,3} to PCI parameters
firmware.c: enw file, move PAL/SAL implementation there
pci.c: new file, move PCI configuration out there
README: add SPCR as a hint to expose serial ports

ski, bootloader: new -initramfs option to support initramfs

initramfs loading is useful as a step towards support for loading of
unmodified upstream kernel. initramfs is a simple interface to get
early userspace into kernel without much of hardware support.

The change implements it on two sides:
- ski implements `SSC_GET_INITRAMFS` SSC call to load initramfs from
  `-initramfs` file.
- ski-bootloader calls `SSC_GET_INITRAMFS` to load initramfs into the
  guest kernel and populates EFI boot info to pass initrd address.

Tested by loading minimal userspace:

    # create initramfs:
    $ ( find . -print0 | cpio --null -ov --format=newc ) | gzip -1 > initramfs.gz
    # pass initramfs:
    bski -initramfs initramfs.gz ski-bootloader vmlinux init=/init TERM=xterm
    ...
    probing initramfs ...
    initramfs loaded
    starting kernel...
    Linux version 4.19.258 (nixbld@localhost)
      (gcc version 13.0.0 20220918 (experimental) (GCC))
        #2 SMP Sun Sep 25 17:31:06 UTC 2022
    ...
    Trying to unpack rootfs image as initramfs...
    random: crng init done
    ...
    Run /init as init process
    Hello from userspace
    / #
